Description: Ostracon, large fragment of the body of a pale red-grey pottery vessel, the exterior is covered with a cream-coloured slip, which has flaked away in a number of places, and faint traces of two lines of black-painted hieratic text.
Bibliographic references: Trismegistos / An interdisciplinary portal of papyrological and epigraphic resources (393977) (http://www.trismegistos.org/text/393977)
